Function: matadjoint
Section: linear_algebra
C-Name: adj
Prototype: G
Help: matadjoint(x): adjoint matrix of x.
  Note: n! must be invertible, where n is the dimension of the matrix.
Doc:
 \idx{adjoint matrix} of $x$, i.e.~the matrix $y$
 of cofactors of $x$, satisfying $x*y=\det(x)*\Id$. $x$ must be a
 (non-necessarily invertible) square matrix of dimension $n$. The algorithm
 assumes that $n!$ is invertible.
